Annuities are rarely a good idea at <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">age 35</ENAMEX> because of the withdrawal restrictions .
But at <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">age 55</ENAMEX> , `` they may be a great deal , '' says Mr. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Wilson</ENAMEX> , the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Columbia</ENAMEX> , <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">S.C.</ENAMEX> , planner .
MONEY MARKET FUNDS :
That 's right , money market mutual funds .
The conventional wisdom is to go into money funds when rates are rising and shift out at times such as the present , when rates seem headed down .
With average maturities of a <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">month</ENAMEX> or so , money funds offer fixed share prices and floating returns that track market interest rates , with a slight lag .
Still , <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">today</ENAMEX> 's highest - yielding money funds may beat CDs over <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">the next year</ENAMEX> even if rates fall , says <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Guy Witman</ENAMEX> , an editor of the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Bond Market Advisor</ENAMEX> newsletter in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Atlanta</ENAMEX> .
